body: Add tests for various unicode methods with start/end parameters where None means "default". Suggested by @scoder  at https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/4737#issuecomment-1100174184.

comment_data.body:
Instead of returning something, I think we can just move the call to `print_all()` into the test helper function as well.

The same applies to the `print()` calls in other tests. I think the only reason why we call `print()` explicitly is the 'u' prefix of unicode strings in Py2, which prevents a straight doctest output comparison.

commit.message:
Allow None to coerce to C types separately from other object values.
This is used by some optimisations for builtins that call C-API functions directly but need to convert None arguments to NULL or special integer values in order to mimic the original Python interface.

Also add and backport the CPython macros for None checks (and True/False, while we're at it):
https://docs.python.org/3/c-api/structures.html#c.Py_Is

Closes https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/4737
See https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/4706

tests/run/unicodemethods: Exercise startswith(start, end) more thoroughly

Verify all combination of start=(None|!None) X end=(None|!None)

tests/run/unicodemethods: Deduplicate tests where via-Cython output is compared to via-Python output

In every test, that is doing such comparison, replace the duplication
with a function that calls both py-function and cy-function, asserts the
result is the same and returns the result.

With this helper we can retain only one doctest entry instead of two for
every tested case. Tests also become a bit more robust because the
possibility of slight unintended error in between py and cy inputs is now
gone.

This refactoring is done in preparation to add more tests for unicode
methods that accept start and stop parameters.

Discussion: https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/4737#issuecomment-1100220378

tests/run/unicodemethods: Exercise *(start,end) more thoroughly

Add more test coverage to tested unicode methods that accept start and
end parameters treated as "default" if passed None.
